
// Playwright Component Object Model — Quiz (20 questions, GIFT, English)

::Q1: What does the Component Object Model (COM) add on top of POM?::
{
=Reusable component classes scoped to a root locator and shared across pages
~Automatic test data generation per page
~A replacement for Page Objects entirely
~A visual regression layer only
}

::Q2: When should you extract a UI block into a component?::
{
=When the same UI block appears on 2+ pages or has its own internal logic
~When it has exactly one locator and no behavior
~Only when it uses XPath selectors
~Only for pages without authentication
}

::Q3: What is the primary difference between BasePage and BaseComponent?::
{
=BaseComponent is scoped to a root locator; BasePage works at full page scope
~BaseComponent handles API requests; BasePage handles UI
~BaseComponent manages test fixtures; BasePage manages reporters
~There is no practical difference
}

::Q4: Why is scoping child locators to the component root important?::
{
=It prevents matching elements outside the component and avoids ambiguity
~It speeds up the Playwright installation step
~It enables XPath only selectors
~It disables auto-waiting
}

::Q5: Which method should component classes prefer for finding elements?::
{
=Use this.root.getBy*() / this.root.locator() inside the component
~Use this.page.getBy*() for all lookups
~Use document.querySelector() through evaluate()
~Use hard-coded XPath expressions
}

::Q6: What is a good COM candidate among these?::
{
=NavBar that appears on every authenticated page
~A single submit button on a unique page
~A one-off hero banner on the home page
~A static image with no interactions
}

::Q7: What does the NavBar component typically expose?::
{
=Navigation links, user menu actions, search, and state helpers
~Only a single click() method
~Only screenshot helpers
~Only API request shortcuts
}

::Q8: In ToastNotification, what does waitForType('success') do?::
{
=Waits until a toast with data-type="success" appears
~Closes any visible toast immediately
~Switches the page to headless mode
~Disables retries for assertions
}

::Q9: What is the responsibility of the Pagination component?::
{
=Navigate between pages, read current/total pages, and check enabled states
~Render table rows dynamically
~Store results in localStorage
~Handle screenshot diffs
}

::Q10: How are nested components used on a page like DashboardPage?::
{
=The page composes shared components (NavBar, Sidebar, Toast) and page-specific ones (DataTable)
~Each page inherits all components automatically without composition
~Components can only be used at the test level, not inside pages
~Nested components are forbidden for maintainability
}

::Q11: What does DataTable.waitForDataLoaded() ensure?::
{
=The table's loading overlay has disappeared (hidden)
~All rows contain at least one cell
~Sorting is set to ascending
~The pagination moved to page 1
}

::Q12: Which pattern is recommended for component collections?::
{
=Wrap the list in a component and return typed sub-components for items
~Return raw ElementHandle[] for iteration
~Access items by CSS classes directly in tests
~Use only nth(0) to pick the first item
}

::Q13: What is a typical method signature for retrieving a typed item from a list?::
{
=getCard(index: number): ProductCard
~getCardByIndex(i: string): Locator
~card(i: number): ElementHandle
~select(index: number): any
}

::Q14: What is the purpose of the AddressForm component?::
{
=Encapsulate labeled inputs, filling, partial updates, and validation getters
~Render server-side templates
~Manage authentication tokens
~Generate CSS styles
}

::Q15: Which API should a Modal component provide?::
{
=waitForOpen(), confirm(), cancel(), close(), getTitleText()
~install(), build(), deploy(), destroy()
~mount(), unmount(), hydrate(), snapshot()
~openWindow(), closeWindow(), minimize(), maximize()
}

::Q16: How does UsersPage.deleteUser(userName) use components together?::
{
=Clicks a row action in DataTable, confirms in ConfirmDeleteModal, waits for success Toast
~Directly calls a REST API and reloads the page
~Uses XPath to remove the row from DOM
~Opens DevTools and runs a script
}

::Q17: What is a COM best practice regarding nesting depth?::
{
=Keep nesting shallow (about 2–3 levels max)
~Nest as many levels as necessary
~Avoid components inside pages entirely
~Use only a single global component
}

::Q18: Which scoping rule is emphasized for components?::
{
=Never reach outside the component root with this.page.getBy*() inside the component
~Always reach outside the root for faster lookups
~Prefer global CSS classes from the page head
~Use window.find() for text search
}

::Q19: What is a good way to test a component that appears on many pages?::
{
=Create a dedicated component test file that navigates to any page where it exists and tests it in isolation
~Only test it indirectly through long end‑to‑end flows
~Mock it entirely and skip UI tests
~Test it once and assume it never breaks
}

::Q20: What is the key benefit of COM across a large suite?::
{
=Eliminates duplication and centralizes maintenance for repeated UI blocks
~Automatically increases test execution speed by 10x
~Removes the need for fixtures
~Generates network mocks for all tests
}

